// difference between package and package-lock.json 

// package.json is the main file that contains all the dependencies and other information about the project.
// package-lock.json is a file that is automatically generated for any operations where npm modifies either the node_modules tree, or package.json.

// What is parcel package?
// Parcel is a zero configuration web application bundler.
// It is used to bundle all the files in the project and create a single file which can be used to run the project.

// What is NPM?
// NPM is a package manager for the JavaScript programming language. 
// It is the default package manager for the JavaScript runtime environment Node.js. 
// It consists of a command line client, also called npm, and an online database of public and paid-for private packages, called the npm registry.  

// What is yarn?
// Yarn is a package manager for the JavaScript programming language. 
// It is the default package manager for the JavaScript runtime environment Node.js. 
// It consists of a command line client, also called yarn, and an online database of public and paid-for private packages, called the yarn registry.


// What is difference between npm and yarn?


// What is a package?
// A package is a directory that contains all the files that are required to run the project. 
// What is a package-lock.json file?
// A package-lock.json file is a file that is automatically generated for any operations where npm modifies either the node_modules tree, or package.json. It describes the exact tree that was generated, such that subsequent installs are able to generate identical trees, regardless of intermediate dependency updates.
// What is a package.json file?
// A package.json file is a file that contains all the information about the project.
// What is a node_modules folder?
// A node_modules folder is a folder that contains all the packages that are required to run the project. 

